1.10	Byrd,_Robert	Robert Byrd	Robert Carlyle Byrd (born Cornelius Calvin Sale, Jr.; November 20, 1917 â€“ June 28, 2010) was a United States Senator from West Virginia. A member of the Democratic Party, Byrd served as a U.S. Representative from 1953 until 1959 and as a U.S. Senator from 1959 to 2010. He was the longest-serving senator and the longest-serving member in the history of the United States Congress.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Robert_Byrd_official_portrait.jpg/220px-Robert_Byrd_official_portrait.jpg
